["Luther M. Turton (May 22, 1862 - April 27, 1925[1]) was an architect in Napa, California.  A number of his works are listed on the National Register of Historic Places.","His full name was Luther Mark Turton.","He was born in North Bend, Nebraska.[1]","Also, outside of Napa, he designed:","and he also designed buildings in Coluso, Yolo and Solano counties.[1]","He was also superintendent of construction on several buildings, including the Bank of Napa building, the First National Bank building in Napa, and two grammar school buildings.[1]","This article about a United States architect or architectural firm is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it."]